Create a symbolic link named __ls__ to /bin/ls

bash
Copy
Edit
#!/bin/bash
ln -s /bin/ls __ls__
⚠️ Correction: You likely meant symbolic link (-s), not hard link. ln alone creates a hard link, but ls is in a separate filesystem, which might cause errors without -s.

